observations.recommendation:
a. Prioritize the conduct of one-time cleansing of PPE accounts as soon as possible by creating an Inventory Committee composed of adequate number of members to be able to complete the physical inventory in three months or less;
b. Instruct the newly created Inventory Committee, GSO and the Accounting Unit to perform the preliminary activities through preparation of required reports such as latest RPCPPE, Inventory Count Form and PPELCs and reconcile their records before the actual physical inventory; and
c. Cause the preparation of PIP containing, at the least, the specific activities, assignments/duties of the Committee members, the cut-off date and a schedule specifying the dates and locations of the inventory taking activities from start up to the targeted completion of the physical inventory to be submitted to the Audit Team at least ten (10) calendar days before the scheduled inventory taking activities.

a. Municipal Accountant to strictly monitor the funds under LDRRMF for any unutilized amount that will pass the five-year retention period and immediately transfer the unexpended balance in CY 2017 after determining the same to the unappropriated surplus of the General Fund which shall be made available for other social services after subsequent enactment by the Local Sanggunian in compliance with section 5.1.13 of COA Circular No. 2012-002;
b. Municipal Accountant to prepare and maintain separate subsidiary ledger per year of transfer to the STF to ensure the proper monitoring of the five-year retention period;
